caption: A high-school guidance counselor speaks to a student.
exif: {"Image ImageDescription": "**HOLD FOR STORY BY CHIRISTINE ARMARIO**In this Thursday, May 26, 2011 photo, high school guidance counselor Roslyn Wagner, rear, talks with Jessica Hujber, 15, at Cooper City High School in Cooper City, Fla. Nationwide, the amount of time students are getting with a counselor to help determine their higher education and career goals is slim. The average middle or high school counselor has nearly 500 students.
